title: VisualHub 1.35
description:
Thanks go to ccMon for providing this.


VisualHub bridges the gap between numerous complicated video formatting standards, and people that just want to get the job done - just what you would expect from the Mac.

If you're looking for something a little more flexible, VisualHub's up for that challenge too. An extensive Advanced panel lets you change all pre-set aspects of encoding...and then some.


The last commercially available version of this is 1.34 as the developer has ended this project.
A compression engine is included which must be placed in the /Library/Application Support obtained from the Macintosh HD not the User Account.

You can use the registration details from version 1.34 on Serial Box.
